claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A table presenting demographic and clinical characteristics of participants in two vaccine groups (recombinant vaccine vs. standard-dose vaccine) and overall (N=675,252), including counts and percentages by sex, race/ethnic group, comorbid conditions, and prior-year influenza vaccination. The table presents only participant demographics and clinical characteristics; it contains no data or statements about antigenic matching to WHO- or FDA-selected flu strains and therefore does not support the claim. Note: Confidence limited to visible content; details on antigenic match are not addressed in this table.
